169 approval of the educational authority.
170 (3) Sick leave days borrowed from the sick leave bank
171 shall be repaid to the sick leave bank monthly as re-earned by
172 the participating member. Upon the resignation or other
173 termination of an employee who has an outstanding loan of sick
174 leave days, the value of the loan shall be deducted from the
175 final paycheck at the employee's prevailing rate of pay.
176 (4) A participating member of the sick leave bank shall
177 not be allowed to accumulate more days than allowed in Section
178 16-1-18.1, including days in the sick leave bank.
179 (5) Employee membership in the sick leave bank shall be
180 voluntary.
181 (6) Any alleged abuse of the use of the sick leave bank
182 shall be investigated by the applicable sick leave bank
183 committee. On the finding of wrongdoing, the participating
184 member shall repay all of the sick leave credits drawn from
185 the sick leave bank and be subject to other appropriate
186 disciplinary action as determined by the localeducational
187 authority.
188 (7) Upon retirement or transfer of the sick leave bank
189 member, days on deposit with the sick leave bank shall be
190 withdrawn and transferred with the employee or made accessible
191 for retirement credit, as applicable.
192 (8) Before being eligible to use catastrophic sick
193 leave days, the participating member of the sick leave bank
194 shall first borrow and utilize days from the sick leave bank,
195 up to a maximum of 15 days. However, if the participating
196 member later qualifies for catastrophic sick leave, donated
