225 leave bank to be designated for a specific employee for use
226 against a catastrophic illness as defined by this section. A
227 donating employee shall not be required to donate a minimum
228 number of catastrophic days to the sick leave bank. The
229 recipient employee may use catastrophic sick leave days for
230 himself or herself or for other covered personsindividuals as
231 provided in Section 16-1-18.1. Before sick leave days for a
232 catastrophic illness may be used by a recipient employee, the
233 recipient employee shall have first exhausted all sick and
234 personal leave. Donated days shall become available for use by
235 the particular employee who shall not be required to repay the
236 days. Any employee who donates sick leave days to the sick
237 leave bank for a particular employee suffering from a
238 catastrophic illness shall be clearly informed that the
239 donated days are not to be recovered or returned to the donor.
240 If a particular employee does not require all of the days
241 donated to the credit of the employee, the days shall revert
242 to the credit of those employees who donated the days in
243 accordance with the guidelines adopted by the sick leave bank
244 committee. No employee may donate more than 30 sick leave
245 days, exclusive of the provisions of subsection (e), to the
246 sick leave bank for the catastrophic sick leave of any one
247 employee. A sick leave bank is authorized to may donate sick
248 leave days to another sick leave bank for use by a particular
249 employee who is suffering a catastrophic illness. An employee
250 must be a participating member of the sick leave bank to
251 donate or receive catastrophic sick leave days.
