267 (h)Compliance required. If an authority fails to comply
268 with this section within 30 calendar days after receiving the
269 petition to establish a sick leave bank, the State
270 Superintendent of Education (for the public schools), the
271 Chancellor of Postsecondary Education (for the two-year
272 postsecondary schools), or the president of the governing
273 board of trustees (for four-year colleges and universities)
274 shall investigate the situation and shall immediately take due
275 and appropriate steps to ensure compliance with this section."
